1
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:13,888
[Dustin] <i>Jonathan! Nancy! Jonathan!</i>

2
00:00:14,764 --> 00:00:16,348
Jonathan! Nancy!

3
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:17,641
[intense music playing]

4
00:00:17,642 --> 00:00:19,435
[grunting] What the hell are you doing?

5
00:00:19,436 --> 00:00:22,688
Listen to me! Don't touch anything!

6
00:00:22,689 --> 00:00:24,232
[music ends]

7
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:34,325
[rumbling]

8
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:37,787
Maybe you missed?

9
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:42,292
[crackling]

10
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:56,722
- Maybe we should, uh...
- Yeah.

11
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,182
[Nancy screams]

12
00:00:58,183 --> 00:01:00,143
[both grunting]

13
00:01:00,977 --> 00:01:02,979
[dramatic music playing]

14
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:31,299
- [doorbell ringing]
- [urgent knocking]

15
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:33,718
[knocking continues]

16
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:36,262
[doorbell rings]

17
00:01:40,725 --> 00:01:43,352
Before you say anything,
I know it's 5:00 in the morning,

18
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:45,395
but I need you
to build me a telemetry tracker.

19
00:01:45,396 --> 00:01:47,272
What? Erica, it is--

20
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:49,358
Five in the morning.
She led with that, buddy.

21
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,610
I'm sorry. Who are you?

22
00:01:51,611 --> 00:01:53,737
- My uncle.
- Babysitter. Babysitter.

23
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:55,114
Who is it, snookums?

24
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:59,034
It's okay, sugar lump. Go back to bed.
I'll just be one second.

25
00:01:59,035 --> 00:02:00,327
Okay.

26
00:02:00,328 --> 00:02:01,662
The librarian?

27
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:03,831
You get too loud in the sack,
she shush you?

28
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:10,170
Okay, listen. You and whoever you are,
this is highly inappropriate.

29
00:02:10,171 --> 00:02:12,340
I will see you in class, Erica.

30
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:15,343
Dustin is in danger.

31
00:02:16,010 --> 00:02:18,137
Danger? What kind of danger?

32
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,847
Like the life or death kind.

33
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:23,016
What do you say, snookums?
You gonna keep playing with your bookworm,

34
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:26,062
or you gonna build us our tracker
and save your star student?

35
00:02:29,232 --> 00:02:30,233
[Steve] Henderson!

36
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:32,276
- Dustin!
- [groans]

37
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:34,736
Dustin. Hey. What the hell was that?

38
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:36,989
Was that the shield generator?
Did they find it?

39
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,324
I was wrong.

40
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:40,285
I was terribly,

41
00:02:41,619 --> 00:02:43,036
catastrophically wrong.

42
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:44,204
What?

43
00:02:44,205 --> 00:02:46,332
After you left, I found a journal.

44
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:48,626
<i>Brenner's journal.</i>

45
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:53,380
<i>The key to destroying that wall
is in this lab,</i>

46
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:56,049
<i>but it is not a shield generator.</i>

47
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:58,636
It isn't dark magic. Vecna didn't make it.

48
00:03:02,056 --> 00:03:03,391
Science did.

49
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:07,979
<i>Theoretical physicists call it
exotic matter.</i>

50
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:12,065
A single source of energy
that is holding that giant wall together,

51
00:03:12,066 --> 00:03:14,569
and I think Nancy just shot it.

52
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:28,540
[Steve] <i>How is that bad? That's why
we're here, to get through this wall.</i>

53
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:30,626
- [Dustin] You are not listening!
- I am listening.

54
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:33,253
Vecna didn't make the wall.
So he isn't on the other side,

55
00:03:33,254 --> 00:03:36,299
which means Holly and the missing kids
aren't either. Nobody is.

56
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:39,636
Then what the hell is
on the other side of that wall?

57
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:51,105
Why'd it stop?

58
00:03:57,779 --> 00:04:00,031
Dustin, what's on the other side
of the wall?

59
00:04:00,823 --> 00:04:01,658
Death.

60
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:06,120
Whoa.

61
00:04:11,834 --> 00:04:14,504
- Come on! Come on, let's go!
- [Eleven exhales intensely]

62
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:16,798
Hurry! Hurry! Hurry!

63
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:18,633
Let's go! Let's go!

64
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:20,468
Get down! Get down!

65
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:27,892
[all grunting]

66
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,396
This whole time,

67
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:35,650
<i>everything we have ever assumed
about the Upside Down has been</i>

68
00:04:36,484 --> 00:04:37,944
dead wrong.

69
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:44,533
[Hopper] The gate!

70
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:45,743
The gate!

71
00:04:46,869 --> 00:04:48,662
I can clear a path!

72
00:04:48,663 --> 00:04:52,833
No, no, no!
You stay behind... stay behind me!

73
00:04:52,834 --> 00:04:54,919
No! Goddamnit!

74
00:04:56,045 --> 00:04:58,381
[epic music playing]

75
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,346
[Hopper] No!

76
00:05:06,014 --> 00:05:07,056
No! No!

77
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:17,108
[grunting]

78
00:05:19,777 --> 00:05:22,404
This place, the Upside Down,

79
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:25,991
<i>it isn't another dimension.
It's not another world.</i>

80
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:27,701
<i>It's a wormhole.</i>

81
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:28,786
A bridge

82
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:33,790
between two points in time and space,
between our world and another.

83
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:35,459
And if the bridge collapses?

84
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,378
It will take us with it.

85
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:41,049
All of us.

86
00:06:13,247 --> 00:06:15,208
[synth theme music playing]

87
00:07:16,352 --> 00:07:18,353
[wind rustling grass]

88
00:07:18,354 --> 00:07:20,690
[cicadas chirping]

89
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,902
[intense music playing]

90
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,447
[both panting]

91
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:42,503
Go, go, go, go!

92
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:50,386
Are you okay? Are you okay? It's okay.

93
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:53,305
We're safe here.
He can't get us here, okay?

94
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:54,390
Max...

95
00:07:56,058 --> 00:07:57,768
[foreboding music playing]

96
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:05,109
Holly!

97
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:06,861
[Max] Come on.

98
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:14,076
[gently] Holly, sweetheart.
Stop, or I'll hurt her.

99
00:08:16,204 --> 00:08:20,416
I know you believe Max is your friend.

100
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:25,253
But she has tricked you, Holly.
She has corrupted your mind.

101
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:27,214
She is a liar.

102
00:08:27,215 --> 00:08:29,633
No! No, you're the liar!

103
00:08:29,634 --> 00:08:32,010
I saw you! I saw what you really are!

104
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:35,305
You're a monster! A disgusting monster!

105
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:36,848
[angrily] Holly!

106
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:40,519
If you don't come back with me right now
and rejoin the other children,

107
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:43,272
I will have no choice but to hurt Max.

108
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:49,152
I may even have to kill her.

109
00:08:49,153 --> 00:08:51,405
Then why don't you? Huh?

110
00:08:52,156 --> 00:08:53,073
I'm right here.

111
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:54,908
Oh, that's right.

112
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:59,288
You're too scared of a stupid cave,
you goddamn coward!

113
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:02,792
Things have changed, Max.

114
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:07,255
There are now other ways to get to you.

115
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:08,923
And Holly?

116
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:13,177
When your new friend begins to suffer,

117
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:16,180
and she will suffer,

118
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:20,184
you can either return to me
and end her suffering,

119
00:09:21,018 --> 00:09:23,396
or you can watch your new friend die.

120
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:25,982
Her life is in your hands.

121
00:10:10,401 --> 00:10:14,946
[Lucas] <i>Can someone please explain to me
what the hell happened out there?</i>

122
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:18,742
We burnt out the particles.
I watched them fly up the tower.

123
00:10:18,743 --> 00:10:21,244
- I mean, you guys saw that, right?
- Hard to miss.

124
00:10:21,245 --> 00:10:23,622
So Will should be unplugged
from the hive mind.

125
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,790
- Theoretically.
- But why didn't he wake up?

126
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:27,751
How did he see Max if she's with Holly?

127
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:30,629
Is this real?
Is Vecna messing with us again?

128
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,505
This makes no goddamn sense!

129
00:10:32,506 --> 00:10:37,093
The doctors, they never understood
why Max was in the coma, right?

130
00:10:37,094 --> 00:10:38,721
What? No. Why?

131
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:43,933
Okay. Okay, okay, okay, okay.

132
00:10:43,934 --> 00:10:47,729
So let's just assume for a second
that everything that Will saw was real.

133
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:50,065
- He saw Max. He saw Holly.
- Yeah, but how?

134
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:53,194
I'm getting to that. Let's say that, uh...

135
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:55,320
this is Will,

136
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:58,823
and this is Holly.

137
00:10:58,824 --> 00:10:59,784
And...

138
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:03,621
uh, this, of course, is Max.

139
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:07,415
They're in three disparate locations,
the Squawk, the hospital,

140
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:09,751
and some presently unknown place
in the Upside Down. Right?

141
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,044
- Right.
- Yeah.

142
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:14,798
But they share one very essential thing
in common.

143
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:16,217
They're all unconscious.

144
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:20,179
What happens when Vecna captures you?

145
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:22,055
You go into a trance.

146
00:11:22,056 --> 00:11:24,224
Which would look
a heck of a lot like a coma.

147
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:27,477
No wonder the doctors are so clueless.
Max was never in a coma.

148
00:11:27,478 --> 00:11:29,188
She was in a trance.

149
00:11:29,772 --> 00:11:32,692
Just like Will. Just like Holly.

150
00:11:33,275 --> 00:11:36,486
It is hitting me
like a Whitney Houston high note.

151
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:38,155
What if their minds...

152
00:11:39,281 --> 00:11:40,700
are all in the same place?

153
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:43,077
In Vecna's mind.

154
00:11:44,453 --> 00:11:45,538
Imprisoned.

155
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:48,289
At least, they were.

156
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:49,582
If Will's right,

157
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:53,753
then Max and Holly
are now making a prison break.

158
00:11:53,754 --> 00:11:55,296
And if they succeed,

159
00:11:55,297 --> 00:11:58,759
they will return to their physical bodies,

160
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:02,387
and Max will come back to life.

161
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:05,265
And they'll have been
in Vecna's mind, literally.

162
00:12:05,266 --> 00:12:07,308
They'll know everything.
They'll know where Will is.

163
00:12:07,309 --> 00:12:09,602
- Where the kids are.
- They might even know what he's planning.

164
00:12:09,603 --> 00:12:12,731
- That's endgame.
- The fate of the planet may very well rest

165
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:16,401
in the hands of your comatose girlfriend
and your baby sister.

166
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:18,319
It's worth one more shot, right?

167
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,946
- Can you drive?
- Not legally.

168
00:12:19,947 --> 00:12:22,115
Good enough.
Take Joyce's car. Do not get pulled over.

169
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:23,700
Get to Max. I'll stay with Will.

170
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:24,785
Okay.

171
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:46,515
[foreboding music playing]

172
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:51,187
[gasps]

173
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:54,774
[slithering]

174
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:06,160
Do you remember this place...

175
00:13:07,661 --> 00:13:08,662
William?

176
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:13,124
No, no, no...

177
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:16,837
- Does it... bring back...
- No.

178
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:22,593
memories?

179
00:13:23,719 --> 00:13:25,638
Max, Holly...

180
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:28,808
They got away, didn't they?

181
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:32,227
Did the leg slow you down?

182
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:35,397
You think you are clever, don't you?

183
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:41,320
But remember, I am the one.

184
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:44,365
The one who invited you in.

185
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:48,285
You were my vessel.

186
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,746
My spy.

187
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:54,083
My builder.

188
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:56,377
Builder?

189
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:03,217
How do you think the tunnels came to be,
William?

190
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:08,888
You built them

191
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:13,561
<i>each and every night you slept.</i>

192
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:22,820
There is much power within you.

193
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:26,365
But make no mistake, boy.

194
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:30,326
They are my powers,

195
00:14:30,327 --> 00:14:34,623
and they are stronger than ever before.

196
00:14:38,961 --> 00:14:41,546
Much stronger.

197
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:47,052
[pulsating]

198
00:14:51,974 --> 00:14:54,268
Now, at last, it is time.

199
00:14:55,394 --> 00:15:01,066
Time for my vessels
to lead us to a new world.

200
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:04,403
A better world.

201
00:15:05,321 --> 00:15:09,991
Too bad your world will never exist,

202
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:13,078
now that Max has one of your vessels.

203
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:17,790
There are ways
to smoke a fox from its den, William.

204
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:20,293
And you are going to help me.

205
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:25,048
You are going to be my spy

206
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:29,093
one last time.

207
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:30,095
No.

208
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:31,555
Never.

209
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:44,777
The more you resist...

210
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:48,738
the more this will hurt.

211
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:51,158
[Will wheezing]

212
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:59,166
[groaning]

213
00:16:01,794 --> 00:16:03,796
[screaming]

214
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:16,767
Stupid.

215
00:16:21,772 --> 00:16:23,106
- Hey!
- What are you doing?

216
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:24,565
Seeing if he's still out there.

217
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:25,858
- He's not.
- How do you know?

218
00:16:25,859 --> 00:16:28,695
Because he knows he can't get us in here.
Let's go.

219
00:16:28,696 --> 00:16:32,031
He said that things had changed,
that there were other ways.

220
00:16:32,032 --> 00:16:35,159
Yeah, and he's totally full of shit.
You should know this by now.

221
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:39,914
So we're supposed to what?
Just do nothing? Accept our fate?

222
00:16:39,915 --> 00:16:41,374
No, we're not accepting shit.

223
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:43,710
We're just staying alive
until we're rescued.

224
00:16:43,711 --> 00:16:45,795
- Rescued by Eleven?
- Mm-hmm.

225
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:47,255
How do you know that was even her?

226
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:49,632
Unless you know somebody else
with psychic powers

227
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:52,176
who's able
to remotely infiltrate Vecna's mind,

228
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:56,305
fight him off, communicate through him
to tell us to run, then it had to be El.

229
00:16:56,306 --> 00:16:59,475
Which means she knows we're here,
and she'll come and she'll save us.

230
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:01,644
Now, can you please stop pacing?

231
00:17:01,645 --> 00:17:04,272
Seriously, you're starting
to remind me of your brother.

232
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:05,607
[Holly sighs]

233
00:17:08,235 --> 00:17:09,278
Thank you.

234
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:17,952
[Holly] Why can't Henry
come in here anyway?

235
00:17:17,953 --> 00:17:19,246
[Max] I don't know.

236
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:22,750
You've had two years with nothing to do.

237
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,461
You must have a theory.

238
00:17:28,797 --> 00:17:31,967
If we're just waiting,
we might as well talk.

239
00:17:38,766 --> 00:17:40,141
- This prison...
- Camazotz.

240
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:42,269
Camazotz. Sure.

241
00:17:44,521 --> 00:17:47,232
It's made up of Henry's memories, right?

242
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:50,443
Including this cave.

243
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:54,198
So I figure it's like,

244
00:17:54,698 --> 00:17:56,908
I don't know,
a memory that, for whatever reason,

245
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:59,328
Henry doesn't want to face.

246
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:01,747
Something traumatic.

247
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:07,711
Except there's nothing in here
that is even remotely scary, so...

248
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:09,630
maybe not.

249
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:13,509
Anyway, that's my theory.

250
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:16,011
I like it.

251
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:19,389
Thanks.

252
00:18:19,973 --> 00:18:22,851
And if you're right,

253
00:18:24,436 --> 00:18:27,439
maybe we can escape through this memory.

254
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:29,358
- What?
- Okay, so...

255
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:33,486
My house, your attic,
those were traumatic memories too,

256
00:18:33,487 --> 00:18:35,446
and they led us out of Camazotz.

257
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:38,074
So maybe Henry's memory can too.

258
00:18:38,075 --> 00:18:41,035
First of all, there's nothing in here,
as I said.

259
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:43,955
Secondly, our memories
weren't simply traumatic.

260
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:47,542
They were memories of the precise moment
that Henry stole our minds.

261
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:49,710
And he can't steal his own mind, can he?

262
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:53,214
- How do you know?
- Because that makes no sense.

263
00:18:53,215 --> 00:18:55,551
And everything in this place makes sense?

264
00:18:57,719 --> 00:18:58,720
I mean,

265
00:18:59,721 --> 00:19:01,348
maybe there's like a...

266
00:19:02,182 --> 00:19:04,976
a secret passageway or something.

267
00:19:04,977 --> 00:19:08,355
Right, yes, I totally forgot
about the secret passage.

268
00:19:12,234 --> 00:19:13,234
What about out there?

269
00:19:13,235 --> 00:19:15,612
Sand. Lots of sand.

270
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:17,488
- You've searched it?
- Yes.

271
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:19,366
- All of it?
- It goes on for miles.

272
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:20,951
So, no.

273
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:25,454
You are not going out there.

274
00:19:25,455 --> 00:19:29,333
Holly, we're staying here,
and we wait for Eleven, end of story.

275
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:30,751
I don't think Henry was bluffing

276
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:32,920
when he said
there's another way to get to you.

277
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:36,133
We have to find a way out of here
before that happens.

278
00:19:36,925 --> 00:19:37,843
You coming?

279
00:19:38,427 --> 00:19:41,180
Or are you gonna let
a child head into the desert unsupervised?

280
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:43,764
[Max] I take it back.

281
00:19:43,765 --> 00:19:47,311
You don't remind me of your brother.
You <i>are</i> your brother!

282
00:19:56,486 --> 00:19:58,488
[vehicle approaching]

283
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:02,242
Joyce?

284
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:04,995
Did someone call the funeral home?

285
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:09,249
[uplifting music playing]

286
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:17,716
Mike.

287
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,261
[Mike] El!

288
00:20:22,262 --> 00:20:23,555
Oh, Mike...

289
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:32,064
[Hopper] I'm here now.

290
00:20:32,981 --> 00:20:34,315
You're okay.

291
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:35,566
I'm okay.

292
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,567
[car door closes]

293
00:20:36,568 --> 00:20:38,070
This is Kali,

294
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:39,862
my sister.

295
00:20:39,863 --> 00:20:41,615
And this must be the famous Mike.

296
00:20:42,741 --> 00:20:44,659
I don't... I don't understand.

297
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:48,163
[Hopper] It's a long story.
Probably best just to tell it once.

298
00:20:49,164 --> 00:20:51,124
Where's the rest of our greeting party?

299
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:57,089
He's just in here.

300
00:21:04,471 --> 00:21:05,806
[Hopper] Oh, Jesus.

301
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:08,099
How long has he been like this?

302
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,268
A few hours.

303
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:13,021
Do you think you can find him?

304
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:21,612
Any clue in there about how long
it takes a wormhole to collapse?

305
00:21:21,613 --> 00:21:22,697
Ten minutes, maybe 20?

306
00:21:22,698 --> 00:21:24,865
I thought it'd be instantaneous.
Clearly not.

307
00:21:24,866 --> 00:21:27,076
- Why do you sound disappointed?
- I'm not disappointed.

308
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,911
- You sound disappointed.
- I'm confused.

309
00:21:28,912 --> 00:21:31,289
As far as I see it,
there are two possibilities.

310
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:34,000
Either this is the afterlife,
and you and I are spirits.

311
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:35,126
- Which seems unlikely.
- Ooh.

312
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:39,422
Or Nancy didn't completely destroy
the exotic matter.

313
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:42,800
Because if she did, the walls
of the wormhole would have collapsed.

314
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:44,927
And we would have been sucked
into oblivion.

315
00:21:44,928 --> 00:21:47,054
Okay, so what
are we waiting around here for?

316
00:21:47,055 --> 00:21:48,180
Where are you going?

317
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:50,933
To see if I can get a damn signal
to find Nancy.

318
00:21:50,934 --> 00:21:52,768
- Steve, wait.
- Let's go, Henderson.

319
00:21:52,769 --> 00:21:54,146
- Wait!
- Let's go.

320
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:57,481
Steve, we don't know if it's safe up here.

321
00:21:57,482 --> 00:21:59,358
You said
the exotic matter wasn't destroyed.

322
00:21:59,359 --> 00:22:01,402
No, I said
it was not completely destroyed.

323
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:03,654
But it was very clearly disturbed.

324
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:07,908
We have no idea what effect this will have
on matter, space-time, gravity.

325
00:22:07,909 --> 00:22:09,744
This whole building could very well be

326
00:22:09,745 --> 00:22:12,455
a highly unstable,
physics-defying death trap.

327
00:22:12,456 --> 00:22:14,165
It seems pretty stable to me.

328
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:16,960
Nancy, you copy? Jonathan, are you there?

329
00:22:17,961 --> 00:22:18,836
Hello?

330
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:20,380
[crackling]

331
00:22:22,549 --> 00:22:24,426
[Dustin] Mother of God.

332
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:34,770
Please tell me they're not up there.

333
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:38,440
[dripping]

334
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:51,953
[grunting]

335
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:01,880
No, no, no, no. No! Nancy!

336
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:07,593
Nancy! No, no, no.

337
00:23:07,594 --> 00:23:08,636
Nancy!

338
00:23:08,637 --> 00:23:10,805
Come on. Nancy.

339
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:12,807
Come on. Come on.

340
00:23:12,808 --> 00:23:15,602
- Are you okay? Are you okay? Okay.
- Yeah. I think so.

341
00:23:16,478 --> 00:23:17,479
What happened?

342
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:19,898
I don't know. I don't know.

343
00:23:21,691 --> 00:23:23,067
I guess we fell.

344
00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:25,194
And also clearly didn't destroy it.

345
00:23:25,195 --> 00:23:26,780
Just pissed it off.

346
00:23:29,032 --> 00:23:30,450
Come on. Let's go.

347
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:34,871
Let's get the hell out of here.

348
00:23:37,499 --> 00:23:39,584
- Where's the door?
- Shit, shit.

349
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:42,337
It's there. Come on.

350
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:46,257
[both straining]

351
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:47,300
Shit!

352
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:53,723
No, no, no! Shit! Shit! No, no, no, no!

353
00:23:56,643 --> 00:23:58,145
Goddamnit.

354
00:23:59,563 --> 00:24:00,856
Come on!

355
00:24:22,002 --> 00:24:25,504
[Mike] Nancy, she didn't leave
a note or anything at the church?

356
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:28,175
No. No, nothing.

357
00:24:28,675 --> 00:24:31,636
Which means they're either
a bunch of inconsiderate pricks,

358
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:34,096
or they got captured by the military.

359
00:24:34,097 --> 00:24:37,808
To put your mind at ease, I am heavily
leaning on the inconsiderate prick theory.

360
00:24:37,809 --> 00:24:41,479
Wait, and that flesh wall you found,
you don't think...

361
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:44,274
They got sucked into
the giant vacuum cleaner? No, I don't.

362
00:24:45,358 --> 00:24:48,528
But I don't really know, Mike.
I'm as confused as you.

363
00:24:49,237 --> 00:24:54,450
This whole thing, Max, Holly, this wall,
it's all gotta connect somehow,

364
00:24:54,451 --> 00:24:55,576
but I can't figure out how.

365
00:24:55,577 --> 00:24:58,787
It's like
there's a missing piece of the puzzle.

366
00:24:58,788 --> 00:24:59,747
A big piece.

367
00:24:59,748 --> 00:25:03,459
The pieces are in Vecna's mind,
and now we finally have a way to get in.

368
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:05,629
[Kali] Except Jane hasn't found anything.

369
00:25:06,463 --> 00:25:09,507
Oh, boy! Here comes Pollyanna
to brighten everybody's day.

370
00:25:09,508 --> 00:25:11,091
She's struggling up there.

371
00:25:11,092 --> 00:25:13,302
Oh, yeah?
Maybe you should give her some time.

372
00:25:13,303 --> 00:25:15,471
She's getting weaker, not stronger.

373
00:25:15,472 --> 00:25:19,016
So you are the expert on El, huh?

374
00:25:19,017 --> 00:25:20,976
You've known her for what,
a day and a half?

375
00:25:20,977 --> 00:25:23,187
Longer than you, actually.

376
00:25:23,188 --> 00:25:26,982
We were raised together,
and her name is Jane.

377
00:25:26,983 --> 00:25:29,026
- Jane Hopper.
- I'm just here to help.

378
00:25:29,027 --> 00:25:32,321
You're just here to help.
Well, I'm sorry I'm all out of gratitude.

379
00:25:32,322 --> 00:25:34,114
I thought you said
this fight was pointless.

380
00:25:34,115 --> 00:25:35,950
You said this whole thing was pointless?

381
00:25:35,951 --> 00:25:37,326
I never said that.

382
00:25:37,327 --> 00:25:40,371
Really? It sure as shit sounded to me
like you did.

383
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:43,249
I leave you alone for two seconds with El,
and you worm your way into her head.

384
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:46,502
She's probably having trouble finding Will
because you've thrown her off track.

385
00:25:46,503 --> 00:25:49,463
She was off track when I met her
because of you.

386
00:25:49,464 --> 00:25:50,881
Because of your lies.

387
00:25:50,882 --> 00:25:52,383
Everything I have done...

388
00:25:52,384 --> 00:25:55,511
...is to protect her.
Keep telling yourself that,

389
00:25:55,512 --> 00:25:58,806
but if you really want to protect her,
she needs to know the truth,

390
00:25:58,807 --> 00:26:01,850
and she needs to be ready
to deal with what's waiting for her

391
00:26:01,851 --> 00:26:03,645
on the other side of this.

392
00:26:04,145 --> 00:26:07,356
Killing Henry won't end this.

393
00:26:07,357 --> 00:26:08,399
What does that mean?

394
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:13,237
It means nothing. She's a child.
She has no idea what she's talking about.

395
00:26:13,238 --> 00:26:15,114
She's talking a bunch of nonsense.

396
00:26:15,115 --> 00:26:17,158
I think you know I'm not.

397
00:26:18,368 --> 00:26:22,706
But just as you lie to Jane,
you also lie to yourself.

398
00:26:25,125 --> 00:26:27,752
You ask why I'm still here?

399
00:26:29,504 --> 00:26:34,467
I'm here to make sure
that this never happens again.

400
00:26:41,057 --> 00:26:41,891
El.

401
00:26:46,313 --> 00:26:47,314
El!

402
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:49,691
Hey, is everything okay?

403
00:26:50,984 --> 00:26:53,694
I can't reach him. He keeps slipping away.

404
00:26:53,695 --> 00:26:55,779
Well, we have plenty of food in there,

405
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:58,949
so eat, rest, and recharge your battery,
and we'll try it again.

406
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:00,035
[Hopper] Or...

407
00:27:00,952 --> 00:27:02,412
we improve your signal.

408
00:27:02,996 --> 00:27:04,788
- The tank.
- Yeah. It'll take a while to set up.

409
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:06,749
But you've gotta
recharge your battery anyway.

410
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:10,545
Plus, that thing was a pain to build,
so I'd like to get some use out of it.

411
00:27:18,386 --> 00:27:21,180
- Doris, I'm gonna sign in later.
- I'm here for emotional support.

412
00:27:21,181 --> 00:27:23,265
Miss Buckley! Miss Buckley!

413
00:27:23,266 --> 00:27:25,560
Oh! You know what?

414
00:27:28,104 --> 00:27:29,229
Hey.

415
00:27:29,230 --> 00:27:30,939
- We need to talk.
- Yeah.

416
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:33,067
- Wait, Robin!
- I've gotta deal with this. Just go!

417
00:27:33,068 --> 00:27:34,151
What about the plan?

418
00:27:34,152 --> 00:27:35,403
Vickie.

419
00:27:37,030 --> 00:27:39,782
Listen, I know you're pissed,
and you have every right to be.

420
00:27:39,783 --> 00:27:41,659
- They're looking for you.
- Who is looking for me?

421
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:43,661
- Security. MPs.
- Why?

422
00:27:43,662 --> 00:27:46,121
- You wanna play dumb?
- I have no idea what you're talking about.

423
00:27:46,122 --> 00:27:47,831
Okay, all right, let me give you a hint.

424
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:50,377
You, Mr. Bailey's room, benzos.

425
00:27:51,086 --> 00:27:52,503
Well, does it ring a bell yet?

426
00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:57,467
Robin, you've gotta start telling me
what is going on with you right now.

427
00:28:03,014 --> 00:28:05,975
Okay, Max, time to come home.

428
00:28:07,143 --> 00:28:10,313
["Running up that Hill (A Deal With God)"
by Kate Bush playing]

429
00:28:21,324 --> 00:28:23,283
[Max] I think
we've been at this long enough.

430
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:25,411
[Holly] We've searched
an inch of this place.

431
00:28:25,412 --> 00:28:27,413
[Max] At last, you get my point.

432
00:28:27,414 --> 00:28:30,541
I've spent I don't know how long
searching out here, but too long.

433
00:28:30,542 --> 00:28:33,627
You're not gonna just suddenly find
something that I haven't, okay?

434
00:28:33,628 --> 00:28:36,547
Did my brother ever tell you
about Uncle Eric?

435
00:28:36,548 --> 00:28:37,798
Uncle Eric?

436
00:28:37,799 --> 00:28:40,384
He's a metal detectorist.
Do you know what that is?

437
00:28:40,385 --> 00:28:41,760
He searches for metal.

438
00:28:41,761 --> 00:28:43,595
Yeah, with his metal detector.

439
00:28:43,596 --> 00:28:47,266
Looking for super old treasures and stuff
that dead people have left in the ground.

440
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:50,477
Anyway, his favorite place to search is
Indiana Beach Amusement Park.

441
00:28:50,478 --> 00:28:52,646
I mean, he searched there for years,

442
00:28:52,647 --> 00:28:55,065
but all he ever found
was a bunch of cheap trinkets.

443
00:28:55,066 --> 00:28:58,652
Then one day, he opens up the newspaper
and boom, front page,

444
00:28:58,653 --> 00:29:00,863
some random tourist found a tin can

445
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:04,032
filled with gold and silver coins
worth like millions of dollars.

446
00:29:04,033 --> 00:29:07,327
Right, so let me guess,
in this scenario, I'm Uncle Eric...

447
00:29:07,328 --> 00:29:08,705
And I'm the tourist.

448
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:20,300
So stupid.

449
00:29:22,844 --> 00:29:24,846
[intriguing music playing]

450
00:29:37,525 --> 00:29:38,943
"M" marks the spot.

451
00:29:43,698 --> 00:29:45,282
- Where are you going?
- I have an idea.

452
00:29:45,283 --> 00:29:47,284
- What idea?
- I'll show you when we're closer.

453
00:29:47,285 --> 00:29:49,870
- Holly!
- You said you wanted to go back.

454
00:29:49,871 --> 00:29:51,581
Well, we're going back.

455
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,294
Guys, if you can hear us, we're coming.
I repeat, we're coming.

456
00:29:57,295 --> 00:30:00,297
Steve, slow down! The higher we go,
the more dangerous it gets.

457
00:30:00,298 --> 00:30:02,049
All the more reason to speed up.

458
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:04,260
We're no use to them if we're dead. Steve!

459
00:30:13,436 --> 00:30:14,729
As I was saying...

460
00:30:17,524 --> 00:30:18,900
[both grunting]

461
00:30:20,318 --> 00:30:21,318
Come on!

462
00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:22,862
[grunts] Damn it!

463
00:30:30,245 --> 00:30:31,662
What are you doing?

464
00:30:31,663 --> 00:30:34,999
A few floors down, it looked like one
of those soldiers cut through that door.

465
00:30:41,965 --> 00:30:43,258
Watch out.

466
00:30:47,846 --> 00:30:49,222
[Jonathan] Shit! Get back!

467
00:30:52,308 --> 00:30:53,976
Shit! Shit!

468
00:30:53,977 --> 00:30:55,228
Oh, God!

469
00:31:01,943 --> 00:31:02,944
Holy shit!

470
00:31:05,572 --> 00:31:08,074
The table! Get to the table!

471
00:31:18,459 --> 00:31:19,544
Now what?

472
00:31:26,009 --> 00:31:28,051
Help! Help!

473
00:31:28,052 --> 00:31:30,429
- Help! Help!
- Steve!

474
00:31:30,430 --> 00:31:33,640
- Help! Help!
- Hey! Help!

475
00:31:33,641 --> 00:31:36,853
- Help! Help! Help!
- Help! Help! Help!

476
00:32:12,013 --> 00:32:13,056
Almost ready out here.

477
00:32:17,143 --> 00:32:18,478
El's gonna fix this.

478
00:32:19,604 --> 00:32:20,813
She's gonna fix it.

479
00:32:25,151 --> 00:32:27,236
It was my idea, Hop.

480
00:32:28,571 --> 00:32:29,447
It was...

481
00:32:30,031 --> 00:32:32,575
my idea for him to go in there.

482
00:32:33,159 --> 00:32:35,619
I don't know. I just thought maybe,

483
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:40,124
after everything that happened,
after everything I saw him do, that...

484
00:32:40,917 --> 00:32:43,251
I started thinking maybe all this time

485
00:32:43,252 --> 00:32:46,672
that I've been trying so hard
to protect him,

486
00:32:46,673 --> 00:32:49,258
I've really just been holding him back

487
00:32:51,010 --> 00:32:52,720
by not listening to him,

488
00:32:53,471 --> 00:32:55,180
not trusting him.

489
00:32:55,181 --> 00:32:56,683
And so if I just...

490
00:32:57,809 --> 00:33:01,436
I don't know.
If I just believed and let go,

491
00:33:01,437 --> 00:33:04,899
that, I don't know,
somehow this could all work out. And...

492
00:33:06,234 --> 00:33:11,363
It's like every choice
that I make is wrong.

493
00:33:11,364 --> 00:33:12,490
I know.

494
00:33:13,992 --> 00:33:18,161
I mean, you can push them into situations
they might not be ready for.

495
00:33:18,162 --> 00:33:20,831
You can be like me,
and you can be overprotective,

496
00:33:20,832 --> 00:33:23,250
and they just resent you for that.

497
00:33:23,251 --> 00:33:25,837
Joyce, one of the joys of being a parent...

498
00:33:28,381 --> 00:33:30,841
is that you'll have a constant reminder
your whole life

499
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:32,719
that every choice you've made

500
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:34,971
has been wrong.

501
00:33:38,516 --> 00:33:40,059
It's not on you, Joyce.

502
00:33:42,979 --> 00:33:44,188
It's not on you.

503
00:33:54,115 --> 00:33:56,117
[water sloshing]

504
00:33:59,871 --> 00:34:02,165
[Mike] That looks nice.
Murray find that for you?

505
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:03,875
Yeah.

506
00:34:05,752 --> 00:34:07,462
Santa Claus has good taste.

507
00:34:11,966 --> 00:34:14,385
Hey. Back at the Squawk,

508
00:34:15,136 --> 00:34:17,596
Kali, she said something weird

509
00:34:17,597 --> 00:34:20,849
about this not being over
even if we kill Henry.

510
00:34:20,850 --> 00:34:22,685
Do you know what she's talking about?

511
00:34:23,728 --> 00:34:25,146
It doesn't matter.

512
00:34:25,855 --> 00:34:27,190
I should warm this up.

513
00:34:27,815 --> 00:34:31,026
Okay, well, if it doesn't matter,
then why was Hop so angry at her?

514
00:34:31,027 --> 00:34:32,402
It's nothing, Mike, really.

515
00:34:32,403 --> 00:34:34,237
- Friends don't lie.
- I'm not lying.

516
00:34:34,238 --> 00:34:37,657
[Mike] You're avoiding. That's a cheat.
I just want to help.

517
00:34:37,658 --> 00:34:40,202
You can't help. Not with this.

518
00:34:40,203 --> 00:34:42,080
Let me be the judge of that.

519
00:34:44,248 --> 00:34:45,416
El, come on.

520
00:34:50,379 --> 00:34:52,923
There's a lab in the Upside Down.

521
00:34:52,924 --> 00:34:55,551
They're restarting Papa's program.

522
00:34:56,511 --> 00:34:58,262
Trying to make new numbers.

523
00:35:01,974 --> 00:35:03,059
The military?

524
00:35:06,437 --> 00:35:07,729
Okay.

525
00:35:07,730 --> 00:35:11,942
So, after we kill Vecna,
we destroy this new lab.

526
00:35:11,943 --> 00:35:13,735
End the program. Like a side quest.

527
00:35:13,736 --> 00:35:16,238
Mike, no, you don't understand.

528
00:35:16,239 --> 00:35:19,449
They don't need a lab to make new numbers.

529
00:35:19,450 --> 00:35:20,827
Henry's blood.

530
00:35:22,495 --> 00:35:23,703
It's in me.

531
00:35:23,704 --> 00:35:25,498
I'm not a monster.

532
00:35:26,749 --> 00:35:28,209
I know that now.

533
00:35:28,793 --> 00:35:30,837
But with me, with my blood,

534
00:35:32,004 --> 00:35:34,382
they can make more monsters.

535
00:35:35,508 --> 00:35:37,718
They can make more Henrys.

536
00:35:38,302 --> 00:35:40,262
The military will always be looking
for you.

537
00:35:40,263 --> 00:35:43,390
We've always known that.
Which is why we aren't staying in Hawkins.

538
00:35:43,391 --> 00:35:46,351
When this is all over, we're leaving.

539
00:35:46,352 --> 00:35:49,312
Escaping to some far off land. Remember?

540
00:35:49,313 --> 00:35:51,566
Somewhere where they can't find us.

541
00:35:52,316 --> 00:35:55,444
Somewhere
where there's at least one waterfall.

542
00:35:56,445 --> 00:35:57,446
Mike.

543
00:35:59,240 --> 00:36:02,493
This isn't like one of your campaigns.

544
00:36:03,619 --> 00:36:05,371
You don't get to write the ending.

545
00:36:06,164 --> 00:36:07,331
Not this time.

546
00:36:09,125 --> 00:36:10,334
Maybe I don't.

547
00:36:11,419 --> 00:36:12,669
But <i>we</i> do.

548
00:36:12,670 --> 00:36:16,215
You, me, Lucas, Will, and Dustin.

549
00:36:16,799 --> 00:36:18,342
Because this is our story.

550
00:36:19,468 --> 00:36:21,804
And it starts with getting Will back.

551
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:35,067
[intense music playing]

552
00:36:38,154 --> 00:36:38,988
[whispering] Max.

553
00:36:49,165 --> 00:36:52,417
You realize you don't need
your spyglass anymore? That's my cave.

554
00:36:52,418 --> 00:36:53,335
Yep.

555
00:36:53,336 --> 00:36:54,962
Also, the cap is still on.

556
00:36:55,463 --> 00:36:56,464
Yep.

557
00:36:57,381 --> 00:36:58,382
Look.

558
00:36:59,717 --> 00:37:00,801
Cap on.

559
00:37:06,098 --> 00:37:08,058
Okay, it's very dark.

560
00:37:08,059 --> 00:37:09,059
But not totally.

561
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:10,644
You see that cutout of light?

562
00:37:10,645 --> 00:37:12,896
It's in the same shape
as the cave entrance.

563
00:37:12,897 --> 00:37:15,523
What are the chances
it cracks in the same shape as the cave,

564
00:37:15,524 --> 00:37:17,317
the cave we know Henry visited?

565
00:37:17,318 --> 00:37:20,695
I think the cap is a map,
a map Henry made when he was young,

566
00:37:20,696 --> 00:37:23,199
a map that'll lead us
to some kind of secret location.

567
00:37:24,033 --> 00:37:26,285
We just have to get the shapes to line up.

568
00:37:27,536 --> 00:37:30,038
And you think in this secret location,
we'll find what?

569
00:37:30,039 --> 00:37:31,581
Henry's traumatic memory?

570
00:37:31,582 --> 00:37:34,168
That. And a way out of Camazotz.

571
00:37:35,044 --> 00:37:37,296
At least... that's my theory.

572
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:39,714
- I like it.
- Thanks.

573
00:37:39,715 --> 00:37:42,008
There's one tiny hole
in your theory, though.

574
00:37:42,009 --> 00:37:44,803
We're near the secret location,
and I've got eyes,

575
00:37:44,804 --> 00:37:48,139
and I still see absolutely nothing
but more goddamn sand--

576
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:49,642
[Holly screaming]

577
00:37:50,977 --> 00:37:51,852
[Max] Hold on!

578
00:37:52,645 --> 00:37:53,896
Hold on!

579
00:37:56,524 --> 00:37:57,900
[both straining]

580
00:38:09,161 --> 00:38:10,413
[both panting]

581
00:38:12,748 --> 00:38:14,083
"M" marks the spot.

582
00:38:22,717 --> 00:38:25,802
Vic, do you want
to maybe verbalize something?

583
00:38:25,803 --> 00:38:28,888
It's just unclear what your face
is trying to communicate here.

584
00:38:28,889 --> 00:38:32,935
I know that it's a lot to absorb,
especially all in one go.

585
00:38:33,561 --> 00:38:35,478
Monsters and alternate dimensions,

586
00:38:35,479 --> 00:38:39,149
and I realize that the drugging
of the Turnbows was a bit unethical--

587
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:44,112
- Okay, stop, Robin. Please, just stop.
- I tried to tell you like a million times.

588
00:38:44,113 --> 00:38:47,991
No, you lied. And then you kept lying
over and over and over again.

589
00:38:47,992 --> 00:38:50,368
- I knew something was wrong.
- I know! I'm sorry!

590
00:38:50,369 --> 00:38:51,911
"Crazy day at work. Call you tomorrow."

591
00:38:51,912 --> 00:38:54,039
"Sorry, there's another crisis
at the Squawk."

592
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:56,291
I mean, who works all night
at a radio station?

593
00:38:56,292 --> 00:38:59,377
And who is stupid enough to believe that?

594
00:38:59,378 --> 00:39:00,962
Apparently me, Vickie,

595
00:39:00,963 --> 00:39:03,548
who's sitting at home,
waiting for the phone to ring

596
00:39:03,549 --> 00:39:05,508
while you're off with your friends,
getting high.

597
00:39:05,509 --> 00:39:06,718
Getting high?

598
00:39:06,719 --> 00:39:10,347
Come on, Robin.
You are going through withdrawal.

599
00:39:10,348 --> 00:39:12,265
You have the wrong idea.
I am not on drugs.

600
00:39:12,266 --> 00:39:14,059
- Right, sorry.
- Just look at me!

601
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:17,729
You have been busy with your friends
hunting monsters!

602
00:39:17,730 --> 00:39:20,190
God! All right,
maybe you even believe it yourself.

603
00:39:20,191 --> 00:39:23,735
With the amount that you were clearly on,
if you just go cold turkey,

604
00:39:23,736 --> 00:39:26,071
it can cause confusion,
paranoia, hallucinations...

605
00:39:26,072 --> 00:39:28,990
These are not hallucinations!

606
00:39:28,991 --> 00:39:30,784
Okay. So let's recap.

607
00:39:30,785 --> 00:39:32,994
- There is a dark wizard...
- Uh-huh.

608
00:39:32,995 --> 00:39:34,454
- ...who is stealing children...
- Yep.

609
00:39:34,455 --> 00:39:36,999
- ...and putting them in a dream world.
- Right.

610
00:39:38,459 --> 00:39:42,128
Vickie, the earth has split in four.

611
00:39:42,129 --> 00:39:44,756
The military has taken over our town.

612
00:39:44,757 --> 00:39:47,301
Is what I'm saying really so insane?

613
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:49,803
Batshit!

614
00:39:49,804 --> 00:39:52,514
You wanna know
what my face is communicating right now?

615
00:39:52,515 --> 00:39:54,099
- Yes.
- Anger.

616
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:59,354
But with a dash,
and it is a very, very reluctant dash,

617
00:39:59,355 --> 00:40:00,314
of worry.

618
00:40:01,232 --> 00:40:03,441
Because as furious
as I am with you right now,

619
00:40:03,442 --> 00:40:06,778
you are not well, Robin,
and you need help.

620
00:40:06,779 --> 00:40:08,738
You need serious help.

621
00:40:08,739 --> 00:40:09,656
[door closing]

622
00:40:09,657 --> 00:40:12,075
- [man] I got a call about some drugs...
- Hang on.

623
00:40:12,076 --> 00:40:13,201
[man] Have you seen her?

624
00:40:13,202 --> 00:40:14,285
[woman] Robin Buckley?

625
00:40:14,286 --> 00:40:17,248
Yes, she's here. I just saw her go
into that room right there.

626
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:20,625
Vickie, I'm so sorry.

627
00:40:20,626 --> 00:40:21,543
Don't.

628
00:40:21,544 --> 00:40:23,129
- But I gotta go.
- Robin!

629
00:40:23,838 --> 00:40:24,755
Hey!

630
00:40:25,923 --> 00:40:27,133
Hey, I'm talking to you!

631
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:28,717
Buckley, stop!

632
00:40:32,638 --> 00:40:34,265
Where do you think you're going?

633
00:40:36,684 --> 00:40:39,018
[both shouting] Help!

634
00:40:39,019 --> 00:40:40,937
- Help!
- Dustin!

635
00:40:40,938 --> 00:40:42,690
- Help! Steve!
- Hey!

636
00:40:46,193 --> 00:40:47,278
Oh, thank you.

637
00:40:49,697 --> 00:40:53,825
Steve, what the hell are you doing?
That's never gonna work. Stop! Stop!

638
00:40:53,826 --> 00:40:57,120
Steve, stop. I'm serious. It's not safe.

639
00:40:57,121 --> 00:40:59,664
- You're gonna fall.
- It's unstable. I got it already, okay?

640
00:40:59,665 --> 00:41:02,333
No, don't! Stop being an asshole!

641
00:41:02,334 --> 00:41:04,127
I'm not. I'm trying to get to them!

642
00:41:04,128 --> 00:41:07,172
You always try to get yourself killed,
and I can't let it happen again.

643
00:41:07,173 --> 00:41:08,840
Stop being so selfish, please.

644
00:41:08,841 --> 00:41:11,801
If you go on there, you're gonna die,
and I can't deal with it again.

645
00:41:11,802 --> 00:41:14,220
You can't die
'cause I can't deal with it again.

646
00:41:14,221 --> 00:41:18,267
Don't let it happen again.
Please. Please don't let it happen again.

647
00:41:19,393 --> 00:41:20,394
Not you.

648
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:22,604
[sobbing] I'm sorry.

649
00:41:22,605 --> 00:41:23,898
No, no, no.

650
00:41:35,743 --> 00:41:37,369
- Help!
- Help!

651
00:41:37,870 --> 00:41:39,997
- Come on! Help! Hey!
- Help!

652
00:41:40,831 --> 00:41:42,040
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

653
00:41:42,041 --> 00:41:43,626
Down. Get down. Get down.

654
00:41:45,252 --> 00:41:47,962
- What are we doing?
- Sitting spreads our weight out.

655
00:41:47,963 --> 00:41:49,923
Mr. Goldstein, physics.

656
00:41:49,924 --> 00:41:52,343
We can buy ourselves some time.

657
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:55,470
They must have heard us by now.

658
00:41:55,471 --> 00:41:57,096
Then why haven't they called back?

659
00:41:57,097 --> 00:41:59,432
And even if they did,
what could they even do?

660
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:01,392
Something. Anything.

661
00:42:01,393 --> 00:42:02,645
Yeah. Yeah.

662
00:42:06,857 --> 00:42:08,024
They're not coming.

663
00:42:08,025 --> 00:42:09,567
Don't say that.

664
00:42:09,568 --> 00:42:11,111
You wanted honesty.

665
00:42:11,737 --> 00:42:13,739
[liquid bubbling]

666
00:42:26,794 --> 00:42:27,836
[sighs]

667
00:42:31,298 --> 00:42:32,758
I hate The Clash.

668
00:42:34,927 --> 00:42:35,928
What?

669
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:40,515
I hate The Clash.

670
00:42:40,516 --> 00:42:44,311
Every time you put them on,
I just try to disassociate from reality.

671
00:42:46,355 --> 00:42:47,438
Yep.

672
00:42:47,439 --> 00:42:48,982
I hate reading your articles.

673
00:42:48,983 --> 00:42:50,900
You don't actually wanna hear my thoughts.

674
00:42:50,901 --> 00:42:52,569
You just want me
to tell you they're great.

675
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:54,028
Because they are.

676
00:42:54,029 --> 00:42:55,154
Most of the time.

677
00:42:55,155 --> 00:42:56,531
Most of the...

678
00:42:56,532 --> 00:42:58,117
Wow. Okay.

679
00:42:59,243 --> 00:43:01,661
I never read <i>Slaughterhouse-Five.</i>

680
00:43:01,662 --> 00:43:04,289
I just read the Cliff notes
and pretended I liked it.

681
00:43:04,290 --> 00:43:05,749
I never read <i>Anna Karenina.</i>

682
00:43:06,458 --> 00:43:08,293
I just read the Cliff notes
and pretended I liked it.

683
00:43:08,294 --> 00:43:10,878
You are always exactly six minutes late,

684
00:43:10,879 --> 00:43:15,008
and I never say anything,
but really, I wanna punch a wall.

685
00:43:15,009 --> 00:43:16,926
I took your pink sweater to Goodwill.

686
00:43:16,927 --> 00:43:18,761
What? I was looking for that.

687
00:43:18,762 --> 00:43:19,971
You know I hate pink.

688
00:43:19,972 --> 00:43:22,473
But I felt guilty afterwards
if that makes you feel better.

689
00:43:22,474 --> 00:43:26,144
I flushed the last bag of
Purple Palm Tree Delight down the toilet,

690
00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:27,895
and I didn't feel guilty about it after.

691
00:43:27,896 --> 00:43:30,148
- Come on.
- I hate it when you're high.

692
00:43:30,149 --> 00:43:31,357
I hate it when you're drunk.

693
00:43:31,358 --> 00:43:34,402
I hate it most of all
when you're high and I'm drunk.

694
00:43:34,403 --> 00:43:35,738
Me too.

695
00:43:36,572 --> 00:43:38,032
Why do we do that?

696
00:43:41,410 --> 00:43:42,494
No idea.

697
00:43:51,211 --> 00:43:52,963
I never applied to Emerson.

698
00:43:55,007 --> 00:43:56,008
I know.

699
00:43:57,885 --> 00:43:59,595
Why didn't you ever say anything?

700
00:44:00,846 --> 00:44:02,264
Why didn't you?

701
00:44:06,060 --> 00:44:07,144
I'm not sure.

702
00:44:12,983 --> 00:44:14,693
I just felt like I was...

703
00:44:16,570 --> 00:44:17,988
doing something wrong.

704
00:44:21,617 --> 00:44:24,787
Like I was going against
the natural order of things.

705
00:44:26,455 --> 00:44:27,665
You know, with...

706
00:44:29,124 --> 00:44:31,584
with what we've been through, it just...

707
00:44:31,585 --> 00:44:33,629
You mean our shared trauma?

708
00:44:35,422 --> 00:44:36,382
Yeah.

709
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:42,428
How could anyone else possibly understand?

710
00:44:42,429 --> 00:44:43,806
It's like this...

711
00:44:44,890 --> 00:44:46,558
this thing that...

712
00:44:47,976 --> 00:44:50,145
ties us together forever.

713
00:44:51,021 --> 00:44:52,022
You know?

714
00:44:54,149 --> 00:44:56,151
It made me feel safe.

715
00:44:57,277 --> 00:44:58,487
But also...

716
00:45:00,864 --> 00:45:01,782
I don't know.

717
00:45:02,783 --> 00:45:04,159
It can be suffocating.

718
00:45:05,911 --> 00:45:06,912
Yeah.

719
00:45:10,916 --> 00:45:12,126
That spring break,

720
00:45:13,293 --> 00:45:15,087
when you were in Lenora...

721
00:45:16,672 --> 00:45:19,298
I didn't really have to stay behind
to work.

722
00:45:19,299 --> 00:45:21,969
I could have had Fred cover for me.

723
00:45:24,430 --> 00:45:26,682
But I think that's why I stayed.

724
00:45:28,183 --> 00:45:29,893
That feeling that I just...

725
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:31,937
I needed space.

726
00:45:34,565 --> 00:45:36,442
Space to be with someone else?

727
00:45:41,989 --> 00:45:43,532
Steve's a good guy.

728
00:45:45,451 --> 00:45:46,744
He makes me laugh.

729
00:45:47,870 --> 00:45:52,458
And, he has better hair than you.
Like, way better.

730
00:45:53,333 --> 00:45:54,376
But no.

731
00:45:56,879 --> 00:45:59,173
No, it was never like that with him.

732
00:45:59,757 --> 00:46:01,632
We're just different people.

733
00:46:01,633 --> 00:46:05,428
You know what he told me?
He wants six kids.

734
00:46:05,429 --> 00:46:06,637
Six kids?

735
00:46:06,638 --> 00:46:08,891
Six little nuggets.

736
00:46:09,767 --> 00:46:11,101
That's like a Happy Meal.

737
00:46:12,686 --> 00:46:14,021
But my point is...

738
00:46:15,481 --> 00:46:18,941
he knows what he wants, and that's great.

739
00:46:18,942 --> 00:46:20,360
But I...

740
00:46:21,195 --> 00:46:22,196
don't.

741
00:46:23,989 --> 00:46:25,282
And...

742
00:46:25,949 --> 00:46:28,911
I guess I was hoping
I'd have time to figure that out.

743
00:46:30,162 --> 00:46:32,705
- But then...
- The world split in four.

744
00:46:32,706 --> 00:46:34,124
And now...

745
00:46:36,835 --> 00:46:37,961
And now...

746
00:46:42,549 --> 00:46:43,383
Hey...

747
00:46:48,764 --> 00:46:50,682
One last confession.

748
00:46:51,767 --> 00:46:53,101
A big one.

749
00:46:59,691 --> 00:47:01,235
John Coltrane.

750
00:47:01,860 --> 00:47:03,362
I figure that...

751
00:47:04,488 --> 00:47:06,156
I've screwed up enough with you.

752
00:47:08,450 --> 00:47:11,328
It'd be nice to get something right
for once in the end.

753
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:13,372
Here.

754
00:47:20,212 --> 00:47:22,506
[melancholy music playing]

755
00:47:31,348 --> 00:47:32,766
Nancy Wheeler.

756
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:36,395
Will you...

757
00:47:38,272 --> 00:47:39,273
not...

758
00:47:40,107 --> 00:47:41,108
marry me?

759
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:50,284
I tried to convince myself

760
00:47:51,451 --> 00:47:53,287
that this would somehow

761
00:47:54,079 --> 00:47:55,621
fix everything.

762
00:47:55,622 --> 00:47:58,333
But it was just gonna make things worse.

763
00:47:59,459 --> 00:48:02,920
Which is why it has been sitting
like a cannonball in my pocket

764
00:48:02,921 --> 00:48:04,506
for the last two days.

765
00:48:05,215 --> 00:48:06,717
[chuckles softly]

766
00:48:07,301 --> 00:48:08,552
So what do you say?

767
00:48:12,723 --> 00:48:14,766
Do you accept my un-proposal?

768
00:48:15,976 --> 00:48:17,936
I accept your un-proposal.

769
00:48:20,355 --> 00:48:21,481
I loved you.

770
00:48:22,816 --> 00:48:23,984
I love you,

771
00:48:24,818 --> 00:48:25,944
Nancy Wheeler.

772
00:48:27,446 --> 00:48:29,823
I love you, Jonathan Byers.

773
00:48:39,875 --> 00:48:41,877
[both crying]

774
00:48:48,133 --> 00:48:50,135
[tinkling]

775
00:49:02,147 --> 00:49:04,149
[hopeful music playing]

776
00:49:05,609 --> 00:49:06,777
Oh my God.

777
00:49:15,911 --> 00:49:16,954
Jonathan!

778
00:49:17,537 --> 00:49:18,538
Oh my God!

779
00:49:20,290 --> 00:49:21,540
[both laughing]

780
00:49:21,541 --> 00:49:22,626
[Jonathan] My God.

781
00:49:49,653 --> 00:49:50,903
Thank you.

782
00:49:50,904 --> 00:49:52,572
I will find him.

783
00:49:54,074 --> 00:49:55,701
I will bring him home.

784
00:50:03,375 --> 00:50:06,211
Okay. Now remember,
if you want out of there...

785
00:50:26,106 --> 00:50:28,108
[tense music playing]

786
00:50:35,574 --> 00:50:37,409
Will, I'm here.

787
00:50:39,327 --> 00:50:41,747
I need you to show me where you are.

788
00:50:43,373 --> 00:50:45,208
Show me where you are.

789
00:50:45,709 --> 00:50:47,377
[slithering]

790
00:51:06,313 --> 00:51:07,314
Will.

791
00:51:10,609 --> 00:51:11,610
Will.

792
00:51:12,194 --> 00:51:13,402
Will, can you hear me?

793
00:51:13,403 --> 00:51:14,738
Will, wake up!

794
00:51:20,702 --> 00:51:22,788
[grunting]

795
00:51:42,933 --> 00:51:44,059
[Max] Can I have that?

796
00:51:51,983 --> 00:51:53,568
Do you think someone fell?

797
00:51:55,821 --> 00:51:57,947
[man panting]

798
00:51:57,948 --> 00:52:00,699
[Holly] It... It's just a memory, right?

799
00:52:00,700 --> 00:52:02,660
Nothing in here can hurt us.

800
00:52:02,661 --> 00:52:04,079
Nothing can hurt us.

801
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:16,842
[panting continues]

802
00:52:18,009 --> 00:52:19,301
Just stay behind me, okay?

803
00:52:19,302 --> 00:52:21,304
- But you said--
- I know what I said.

804
00:52:22,931 --> 00:52:24,224
[man moaning]

805
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:34,776
How did you find me?

806
00:52:37,112 --> 00:52:39,113
[shouting] How did you find me?

807
00:52:39,114 --> 00:52:42,116
He sees us. He sees us.
How does he see us?

808
00:52:42,117 --> 00:52:43,368
I won't hurt you.

809
00:52:44,035 --> 00:52:46,829
Please, mister, don't shoot.

810
00:52:46,830 --> 00:52:48,164
Who are you?

811
00:52:48,165 --> 00:52:50,833
Henry. Henry Creel. I live near here.

812
00:52:50,834 --> 00:52:52,960
- Who sent you?
- Nobody sent me.

813
00:52:52,961 --> 00:52:55,212
- They sent you.
- I was in the caves. I heard a scream.

814
00:52:55,213 --> 00:52:56,505
They sent you!

815
00:52:56,506 --> 00:52:59,676
- You're just confused. You need a doctor.
- [gunshot]

816
00:53:09,019 --> 00:53:10,979
[intense music playing]

817
00:53:11,813 --> 00:53:13,689
[both straining]

818
00:53:13,690 --> 00:53:15,650
Please! Please!

819
00:53:21,948 --> 00:53:24,074
[grunting]

820
00:53:24,075 --> 00:53:25,076
Holly!

821
00:53:26,077 --> 00:53:27,078
Holly!

822
00:53:31,416 --> 00:53:32,417
Shit!

823
00:53:34,336 --> 00:53:36,879
Hey, it's okay. It's okay.

824
00:53:36,880 --> 00:53:41,342
Why did that man try to hurt Henry?
Hurt Henry? He was only trying to help.

825
00:53:41,343 --> 00:53:43,344
- I don't know.
- Is this what made Henry bad?

826
00:53:43,345 --> 00:53:47,140
I don't know. But it's over now, okay?
We have to keep moving.

827
00:53:54,314 --> 00:53:56,316
[Henry crying softly]

828
00:54:13,833 --> 00:54:17,087
["Running up that Hill (A Deal With God)"
by Kate Bush playing in distance]

829
00:54:19,047 --> 00:54:21,174
[intense music continues]

830
00:54:31,643 --> 00:54:32,978
[air hisses]

831
00:54:37,482 --> 00:54:38,691
You were right.

832
00:54:38,692 --> 00:54:41,528
The way out of Camazotz, it's here.

833
00:54:42,988 --> 00:54:47,117
<i>♪ Be runnin' up that road
Be runnin' up that hill ♪</i>

834
00:54:48,827 --> 00:54:50,369
[heart monitor beeping]

835
00:54:50,370 --> 00:54:51,287
Max?

836
00:54:51,288 --> 00:54:53,622
[beeps accelerate]

837
00:54:53,623 --> 00:54:59,379
<i>♪ ...make a deal with God
And I'd get Him to swap our places ♪</i>

838
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:08,554
[Vecna] <i>You are going
to spy for me one last time.</i>

839
00:55:08,555 --> 00:55:09,889
[screaming]

840
00:55:15,145 --> 00:55:18,398
[heart monitor beeping]

841
00:55:20,066 --> 00:55:21,067
Found you.

842
00:55:22,861 --> 00:55:26,488
Will. Will, it's okay.
It's okay. I'm here.

843
00:55:26,489 --> 00:55:27,573
- El...
- I'm here.

844
00:55:27,574 --> 00:55:28,824
El... El...

845
00:55:28,825 --> 00:55:32,411
It's me. It's me.
I'm here to bring you home. It's okay.

846
00:55:32,412 --> 00:55:35,622
I tried to stop him, but I couldn't.

847
00:55:35,623 --> 00:55:36,708
He saw.

848
00:55:37,292 --> 00:55:39,002
He saw what? What did he see?

849
00:55:39,711 --> 00:55:40,628
Max.

850
00:55:41,838 --> 00:55:43,381
He knows where she is now.

851
00:55:44,090 --> 00:55:45,842
And he sent them after her.

852
00:55:46,718 --> 00:55:49,387
They're coming for her. In Hawkins.

853
00:55:53,350 --> 00:55:54,475
- El!
- El, what's up?

854
00:55:54,476 --> 00:55:55,477
Are you okay?

855
00:55:56,227 --> 00:55:57,227
El, what's wrong?

856
00:55:57,228 --> 00:55:59,313
- Is he all right?
- Yeah.

857
00:55:59,314 --> 00:56:01,900
Vecna's going to kill Max.

858
00:56:02,484 --> 00:56:04,568
We have to get to the hospital right now.

859
00:56:04,569 --> 00:56:07,363
Hey! Are you deaf or what?
She's in withdrawal.

860
00:56:07,364 --> 00:56:08,864
- I am not.
- You know what that means?

861
00:56:08,865 --> 00:56:11,033
She needs to be in a hospital,
not a prison.

862
00:56:11,034 --> 00:56:13,160
Would you look at that?
She's in a hospital.

863
00:56:13,161 --> 00:56:16,164
This is Hawkins, Candy Cane.
Not our first junkie.

864
00:56:17,999 --> 00:56:19,042
[gasping]

865
00:56:21,419 --> 00:56:23,338
Power outage in a hospital.

866
00:56:23,922 --> 00:56:26,215
Can't be good for Granny. Not our problem.

867
00:56:26,216 --> 00:56:27,883
You don't understand. We need to evacuate.

868
00:56:27,884 --> 00:56:30,677
We don't need to do shit.
Keep moving, junkie.

869
00:56:30,678 --> 00:56:32,137
I'm not a junkie.

870
00:56:32,138 --> 00:56:34,431
If we don't get everyone
out of here right now,

871
00:56:34,432 --> 00:56:36,475
- we are all going to die.
- [footsteps pounding]

872
00:56:36,476 --> 00:56:39,269
There is nothing you can say
on God's green earth

873
00:56:39,270 --> 00:56:42,981
that is going to keep you out of a cell.
So save your junkie breath.

874
00:56:42,982 --> 00:56:45,859
- We need to evacuate.
- I actually don't need to do shit.

875
00:56:45,860 --> 00:56:47,654
- [screaming]
- [Demo-dog snarling]

876
00:56:48,446 --> 00:56:49,321
Holy shit!

877
00:56:49,322 --> 00:56:50,407
Run!

878
00:56:51,491 --> 00:56:53,326
- [flesh crunching]
- [Robin screaming]

879
00:57:13,513 --> 00:57:15,055
They're not after us.

880
00:57:15,056 --> 00:57:16,098
Huh? What?

881
00:57:16,099 --> 00:57:19,184
They're not after us.
Do you know another way out?

882
00:57:19,185 --> 00:57:21,563
The basement. The basement!
It leads to staff parking.

883
00:57:23,690 --> 00:57:24,691
Okay.

884
00:57:25,233 --> 00:57:27,276
Come on, Lucas, pick up. Pick up.

885
00:57:27,277 --> 00:57:29,362
[phone ringing]

886
00:57:30,280 --> 00:57:32,030
Pick up. Pick up. What are you doing?

887
00:57:32,031 --> 00:57:33,323
- Can those things understand English?
- No.

888
00:57:33,324 --> 00:57:34,993
- Then this doesn't need to be private.
- What?

889
00:57:36,411 --> 00:57:38,620
<i>Lucas, it's Robin.
A Demo is headed your way.</i>

890
00:57:38,621 --> 00:57:41,832
Do you hear me? A Demo is headed your way.
You need to get Max out of there now.

891
00:57:41,833 --> 00:57:43,834
<i>Take the elevator.
They're on the stairwell.</i>

892
00:57:43,835 --> 00:57:45,252
We'll meet you in the basement.

893
00:57:45,253 --> 00:57:47,547
[lights buzzing]

894
00:57:59,350 --> 00:58:00,392
[roaring]

895
00:58:00,393 --> 00:58:03,563
["Running up that Hill (A Deal With God)"
continues on stereo]

896
00:58:12,113 --> 00:58:13,156
Come on. Come on.

897
00:58:15,116 --> 00:58:16,201
[elevator dings]

898
00:58:23,208 --> 00:58:24,292
Shit.

899
00:58:25,543 --> 00:58:26,503
Shit. Come on!

900
00:58:33,051 --> 00:58:35,220
[tense music playing]

901
00:58:43,311 --> 00:58:44,436
[Max straining]

902
00:58:44,437 --> 00:58:46,022
Goddamnit!

903
00:58:47,732 --> 00:58:48,941
It's not budging.

904
00:58:48,942 --> 00:58:51,276
We're just gonna have to try, okay?

905
00:58:51,277 --> 00:58:52,362
Come on.

906
00:58:58,076 --> 00:58:59,076
You good?

907
00:58:59,077 --> 00:59:00,537
- I... I'm good.
- Okay.

908
00:59:04,249 --> 00:59:06,918
- I need you to grab my hand, okay?
- Okay.

909
00:59:11,798 --> 00:59:13,675
[grunting]

910
00:59:30,400 --> 00:59:31,275
Whoa! Jesus!

911
00:59:31,276 --> 00:59:32,818
Okay. They're coming!

912
00:59:32,819 --> 00:59:34,278
- We gotta go!
- [Robin] Which way?

913
00:59:34,279 --> 00:59:35,654
[Demo-dog roaring]

914
00:59:35,655 --> 00:59:38,115
Here! What the hell is going on?

915
00:59:38,116 --> 00:59:39,324
[Demo-dog snarling]

916
00:59:39,325 --> 00:59:41,034
- Here!
- How are they finding us?

917
00:59:41,035 --> 00:59:42,828
I don't know,
but we gotta get out of here.

918
00:59:42,829 --> 00:59:43,787
Okay. Come on.

919
00:59:43,788 --> 00:59:45,706
- Come on. Let's go.
- Go, go, go.

920
00:59:45,707 --> 00:59:48,209
Come on. Shut the door. Shut the door!

921
00:59:49,085 --> 00:59:50,586
- [Demo-dog roaring]
- [yelps]

922
00:59:50,587 --> 00:59:52,714
- [Lucas] Oh, shit.
- [Robin] Go! Just keep going!

923
00:59:53,673 --> 00:59:54,965
- Come on.
- [Lucas] Damn it!

924
00:59:54,966 --> 00:59:56,634
[Robin] We gotta go!

925
00:59:57,719 --> 01:00:00,221
- [Lucas] The door! Open the door!
- Go, go, go!

926
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:03,141
[urgent slamming on door]

927
01:00:05,393 --> 01:00:07,728
Shit. This way, guys! Come on! Come on!

928
01:00:07,729 --> 01:00:08,770
Get down!

929
01:00:08,771 --> 01:00:11,566
["Running up that Hill (A Deal With God)"
continues on stereo]

930
01:00:15,528 --> 01:00:17,988
<i>♪ If I only could... ♪</i>

931
01:00:17,989 --> 01:00:20,783
[whispering] I'm really sorry
I thought you were a druggie.

932
01:00:22,035 --> 01:00:26,623
I'm sorry for lying to you for, like,
a ludicrously extended period of time.

933
01:00:27,123 --> 01:00:30,709
For the record,
I wasn't lying about Enzo's.

934
01:00:30,710 --> 01:00:35,547
And if by some miracle we survive this,
I am going to take you there,

935
01:00:35,548 --> 01:00:39,551
and we are getting dessert. Deal?

936
01:00:39,552 --> 01:00:42,722
<i>♪ Unaware I'm tearin' you asunder
Yeah, yeah, yo ♪</i>

937
01:00:43,556 --> 01:00:45,850
<i>♪ There is thunder in our hearts ♪</i>

938
01:00:53,024 --> 01:00:54,317
[roaring]

939
01:01:03,159 --> 01:01:05,202
<i>♪ It's you and me ♪</i>

940
01:01:05,203 --> 01:01:06,703
[whispering] We have to turn it off.

941
01:01:06,704 --> 01:01:10,291
We can't. We can't.
No. No. Max is coming back.

942
01:01:10,875 --> 01:01:12,043
We have to.

943
01:01:13,044 --> 01:01:14,336
She's coming back.

944
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:16,422
<i>♪ Come on, darlin' ♪</i>

945
01:01:21,344 --> 01:01:22,470
[Holly] Are you okay?

946
01:01:23,930 --> 01:01:24,971
Go.

947
01:01:24,972 --> 01:01:27,974
["Running up that Hill (A Deal With God)"
continues in distance]

948
01:01:27,975 --> 01:01:30,061
[dramatic music overlapping]

949
01:01:35,692 --> 01:01:36,734
Okay.

950
01:01:40,530 --> 01:01:42,407
You ready to go home, tourist?

951
01:01:45,076 --> 01:01:46,035
Yeah.

952
01:01:46,661 --> 01:01:50,330
<i>♪ If I only could make a deal with God ♪</i>

953
01:01:50,331 --> 01:01:53,543
<i>♪ I'd get him to swap our places ♪</i>

954
01:01:54,752 --> 01:01:58,506
<i>♪ Be runnin' up that road
Be runnin' up that hill ♪</i>

955
01:02:00,216 --> 01:02:02,218
[growling softly]

956
01:02:03,803 --> 01:02:07,973
<i>♪ If I only could make a deal with God ♪</i>

957
01:02:07,974 --> 01:02:11,309
<i>♪ I'd get him to swap our places ♪</i>

958
01:02:11,310 --> 01:02:15,772
<i>♪ Be runnin' up that road
Be runnin' up that hill ♪</i>

959
01:02:15,773 --> 01:02:17,859
<i>♪ Be runnin' up that building ♪</i>

960
01:02:38,004 --> 01:02:39,213
[Demo-dogs growling]

961
01:02:43,259 --> 01:02:44,260
[snarling]

962
01:02:47,013 --> 01:02:48,431
[loud buzzing]

963
01:02:51,392 --> 01:02:52,727
[clanging]

964
01:03:01,027 --> 01:03:03,029
[clanging continues]

965
01:03:06,699 --> 01:03:08,701
[Demo-dog growling]

966
01:03:20,171 --> 01:03:21,047
[growls inquisitively]

967
01:03:22,673 --> 01:03:24,300
[Robin and Vickie exclaiming]

968
01:03:31,265 --> 01:03:32,350
[Robin groans]

969
01:03:37,396 --> 01:03:39,398
[uplifting music playing]

970
01:03:50,785 --> 01:03:52,787
[grunting loudly]

971
01:04:02,505 --> 01:04:05,466
["Running up that Hill (A Deal With God)"
continues in distance]

972
01:04:11,681 --> 01:04:15,560
<i>♪ Let's exchange the experience ♪</i>

973
01:04:25,695 --> 01:04:26,737
Lucas.

974
01:04:33,452 --> 01:04:34,996
Holly. Wait.

975
01:04:37,331 --> 01:04:38,373
You can't come with me.

976
01:04:38,374 --> 01:04:41,251
What? What do you mean?

977
01:04:41,252 --> 01:04:42,712
This way leads to me,

978
01:04:43,588 --> 01:04:46,339
to my body, not yours.

979
01:04:46,340 --> 01:04:48,049
You have to find your own way.

980
01:04:48,050 --> 01:04:51,678
How? I don't have Kate Bush.
I don't even know who Kate Bush is.

981
01:04:51,679 --> 01:04:53,680
You don't need Kate Bush
to get out of here.

982
01:04:53,681 --> 01:04:55,765
Turns out, I don't either.

983
01:04:55,766 --> 01:04:58,144
Music isn't the only way back.

984
01:04:58,686 --> 01:05:03,149
You just need something that connects you
to the real world, to home.

985
01:05:03,816 --> 01:05:05,651
Something powerful,

986
01:05:06,235 --> 01:05:07,485
meaningful.

987
01:05:07,486 --> 01:05:11,198
Lucas, when... when he took my hand
in the hospital,

988
01:05:12,158 --> 01:05:14,785
I could feel it. Right here.

989
01:05:16,120 --> 01:05:18,581
But then I could also feel it in here.

990
01:05:19,290 --> 01:05:20,874
But I don't have a boyfriend.

991
01:05:20,875 --> 01:05:22,292
You don't need a boyfriend.

992
01:05:22,293 --> 01:05:24,419
You just need something
that's special to you,

993
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:27,547
something that makes you feel safe,

994
01:05:27,548 --> 01:05:31,677
something that brings you strength,
something that gives you hope.

995
01:05:32,261 --> 01:05:33,470
Holly the Heroic.

996
01:05:33,471 --> 01:05:35,306
She's here with you now.

997
01:05:36,599 --> 01:05:38,767
But she's also with you in the real world.

998
01:05:38,768 --> 01:05:42,771
Wherever you are,
all you have to do is follow her home.

999
01:05:42,772 --> 01:05:43,940
How?

1000
01:05:44,690 --> 01:05:49,612
Just... try and remember
what it is that she means to you.

1001
01:05:50,655 --> 01:05:52,865
She doesn't mean anything important.

1002
01:05:55,076 --> 01:05:56,369
She's just a toy.

1003
01:05:57,453 --> 01:06:00,330
If she's just a toy,
why do you always carry her with you?

1004
01:06:00,331 --> 01:06:01,873
Mike.

1005
01:06:01,874 --> 01:06:05,585
He said that she had divine powers
and that she never gets scared,

1006
01:06:05,586 --> 01:06:09,631
and so if I ever got scared,
I could just... become her.

1007
01:06:09,632 --> 01:06:13,219
But I keep trying, and it never works.

1008
01:06:15,346 --> 01:06:17,348
No matter what I do, I'm still me.

1009
01:06:19,600 --> 01:06:22,185
The girl who needs a stupid night-light.

1010
01:06:22,186 --> 01:06:25,313
When my mom was attacked,
I couldn't save her.

1011
01:06:25,314 --> 01:06:26,690
I couldn't even save myself.

1012
01:06:26,691 --> 01:06:28,359
Holly, get back!

1013
01:06:29,610 --> 01:06:31,528
I just stood there.

1014
01:06:31,529 --> 01:06:33,531
And then when Henry attacked you...

1015
01:06:34,198 --> 01:06:35,824
- Stop!
- [growls]

1016
01:06:35,825 --> 01:06:40,746
I stood there again.
There's nothing heroic about that.

1017
01:06:41,330 --> 01:06:44,207
There was nothing that you could do
in those moments, Holly.

1018
01:06:44,208 --> 01:06:47,378
I mean, you're a Wheeler. You're smart.

1019
01:06:48,129 --> 01:06:51,716
You honestly think that you could've
stopped those monsters with a fire poker?

1020
01:06:52,299 --> 01:06:55,093
And I think you're leaving
a few important things out.

1021
01:06:55,094 --> 01:06:57,887
The day that we met,
you went into the woods

1022
01:06:57,888 --> 01:07:00,557
even though Henry told you
that dangerous monsters live there.

1023
01:07:00,558 --> 01:07:03,018
And then you followed me into the cave

1024
